## 1️⃣ UserActivityModel

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`useractivity` table**.
**Step 1:** It records **user login and logout activity**.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique record id**.
**Step 3:** `userid` tells **which user performed the activity**.
**Step 4:** `status` stores the **activity status** (login/logout).
**Step 5:** `ip` stores the **user’s IP address**.
**Step 6:** `logintime` stores **when the user logged in**.
**Step n:** `logouttime` stores **when the user logged out**.

---

## 2️⃣ TopicModel

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`topics` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **topics used in the system**.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique topic id**.
**Step 3:** `label` stores the **topic name**.
**Step 4:** `icon` stores the **icon related to the topic**.
**Step 5:** `profiletype` tells **which profile type the topic belongs to**.
**Step 6:** `userid` shows **who created the topic**.
**Step n:** `iscustom` tells if the topic is **custom created or system default**.

---

## 3️⃣ TopicAuthorityDistribution

**Step 0:** This model represents a **table storing authority distribution for topics**.
**Step 1:** It shows **how much authority a user has in a topic**.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique record id**.
**Step 3:** `userId` identifies **which user this record belongs to**.
**Step 4:** `percentage` stores **authority percentage**.
**Step n:** `name` stores the **topic or authority name**.

---

## 4️⃣ ToneMaster

**Step 0:** This model represents the **tone master table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **different content tones** used in the system.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique id**.
**Step 3:** `name` stores the **tone name** (example: professional, friendly, motivational).
**Step n:** This table is used when the system **generates content with different tones**.



## 1️⃣ SupportStatusHistoryModel

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`supportstatushistory` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores the **history of status changes for support tickets**.
**Step 2:** `supportId` tells **which support ticket this status belongs to**.
**Step 3:** `status` stores the **current status number (open, closed, etc.)**.
**Step 4:** `active` shows **whether the record is active**.
**Step n:** `createdTime` stores **when the status was recorded**.

---

## 2️⃣ SupportDetails

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`supportdetails` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **extra details or messages related to a support ticket**.
**Step 2:** `supportid` links the record to a **specific support ticket**.
**Step 3:** Fields like `name`, `email`, `phone` store **user contact details**.
**Step 4:** `message` stores the **support message or reply**.
**Step n:** It basically **stores conversation/details for a support request**.

---

## 3️⃣ Support

**Step 0:** This model represents the **main `support` table**.
**Step 1:** When a user **creates a support ticket**, it is saved here.
**Step 2:** `userid` identifies **who created the ticket**.
**Step 3:** `category`, `subject`, and `message` describe the **issue**.
**Step 4:** `attachmentDoc` stores **any uploaded file**.
**Step 5:** `ticketno` stores the **ticket number**.
**Step n:** This table **manages support tickets in the system**.

---

## 4️⃣ SubscriptionPlan

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`subscription_plan` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **different subscription plans offered in the system**.
**Step 2:** `planTitle` and `planDescription` describe the **plan**.
**Step 3:** `planAmount` stores the **price of the plan**.
**Step 4:** `planType` stores the **type of subscription**.
**Step 5:** `planFeatures` stores the **features included in the plan**.
**Step n:** It basically **defines available subscription plans**.

---

## 5️⃣ SubscribtionPlanDetails

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`subscribtionplandetailslist` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **detailed features of subscription plans**.
**Step 2:** `title` and `subTitle` describe the **feature section**.
**Step 3:** `description` explains the **feature in detail**.
**Step 4:** `features` stores the **specific feature name**.
**Step n:** This table **lists features that belong to subscription plans**.

